Class Lass and all others,hi,hope you all have a great Christmas,I think some here are not being honnest,think a couple were not even in Nam,there will always be pain,there is a great benifit in shareing it if done so in good spirits.I remember that when I came back to the states I thought everyone here had taken too many drugs and that they were crazy,wasn't long though before I came to realize that it was I that had returned as a different person,I really was not sure I was even human any more.Today I still experience these same feelings,i've been pretty ill and what I know is that people love me,they simply do not know how to communicate.They are afraid to get too close and the subject matter is way off base,I tell my family and the two friends I see that I am not an egg,just an egghead.When I see something I feel is wrong with others I look inside me,most of the time I find the problem,it's stuck underneath something I have avoided addressing sometime/somewhere in the past and when I get to feeling bad enough I do the right thing and somehow everyone else gets to looking/sounding better.I Love all of you out there and for this I personally thank GOD 1st.&amp; then all of YOU!!!Merry Christmas &amp; Happy New Year's Dan Knight cknightstonemedia.com
